Title: _app.vendor.catalog._index page
Route file: web/routes/_app.vendor.catalog._index.tsx
Suggested path: /app/vendor/catalog

Role/Purpose
- Provide vendor catalog management interface with three tabs: Asset Reviews, Catalog Mappings, and Version History.
- Enable vendors to review asset quality, manage SKU-to-product mappings, and track version changes.

Primary UI Components
- `PageHeader` with title "Catalog Management" and description.
- Optional `Alert` banner when `isSample === true` showing sample dataset message with error details.
- `Tabs` component with three tabs: Asset Reviews, Catalog Mappings, Version History.
- Each tab contains a custom `Table` component from `@/components/ui/table` with relevant columns.
- Asset Reviews table: SKU, Name, Template, Jig, Status (with checks), Reviewer, Updated.
- Catalog Mappings table: Vendor SKU, Product, Template, Jig, Status, Notes, Last updated.
- Version History table: SKU, Version, Status, Note, Actor, Published.
- Status badges with color coding: passed=emerald, warning=amber, failed=rose, draft=slate, ready=sky, published=emerald, deprecated=orange.
- Bulk CSV upload form and manual product creation form (in Asset Reviews tab).

Data Dependencies
- Loader calls three parallel API queries via `Promise.all`: `context.api.assetReview.findMany()`, `context.api.catalogMapping.findMany()`, `context.api.catalogVersion.findMany()`.
- Asset reviews select: `id`, `sku`, `name`, `assetUrl`, `template`, `jig`, `status`, `reviewer`, `updatedAt`, `checks` (first 250).
- Catalog mappings select: `id`, `vendorSku`, `productId`, `productName`, `template`, `jig`, `status`, `notes`, `lastUpdated` (first 250).
- Catalog versions select: `id`, `sku`, `version`, `status`, `note`, `actor`, `publishedAt` (first 250).
- On error, returns sample data arrays (`buildSampleAssets()`, `buildSampleMappings()`, `buildSampleVersions()`) with `isSample: true` and `errorMessage`.
- Records normalized with type guards to ensure type safety.

Actions & Side Effects
- Tab switching updates visible content (client-side).
- Bulk CSV upload form processes CSV data (stub implementation, shows toast feedback).
- Manual product creation form submits via `api.vendorProduct.create()` and navigates to products list on success.
- Alert displays when showing sample data with error message surfaced.
- Relative date formatting uses `date-fns` `formatDistanceToNow` for asset reviews.

Acceptance Criteria
- Loader handles API success and failure gracefully with sample data fallback.
- All three API queries execute in parallel via `Promise.all`.
- Tabs switch correctly between Asset Reviews, Catalog Mappings, and Version History.
- Status badges display with correct colors based on status values.
- Asset reviews show check outcomes (pass/warn/fail) with appropriate icons.
- Catalog mappings show product linkage and mapping status.
- Version history shows actor and published timestamps.
- Bulk CSV upload shows processing status and toast feedback.
- Manual product creation form validates and submits correctly.
- Empty states handle gracefully when no records in a category.
- Relative dates format correctly (e.g., "2 hours ago").

